<event name="SOCIALIZE_DDTHE_FOOLISH_GENERIC_3" unique="true">
	<text>It takes you a moment, but you find the Foolish rummaging through a container in the hold. Sensing your presence, he turns to face you, "Oh, uh, hello... Was thhhhere somethhhhing you needed?" He seems nervous, but you figure he always is.</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>I wanted to see you! What're you doing in here?</text>
		<event>
			<text>He appears to be shocked by that, fidgeting a bit before answering, "I was just, um, a bit hungry... As a mattervirus, thhhhe Soulplague typically lets me get away withhhh eating just about anythhhhing, but... sometimes it craves somethhhhing in particular."</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Something in particular? Like?</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Like... well... cardboard..." The Foolish averts his gaze and sinks a little from where he typically floats in the air, bumping against the floor. "You don't, uh... happen to know where we might keep some, do you, captain?"</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>I can't say I do.</text>
						<event>
							<text>Pressing against the floor harder, he replies, dejected, "Thhhhat's okay, it was a stupid craving anyways... Thhhhanks for wanting to talk to me, at least. See you around, captain..." The Foolish closes the container he'd been rummaging through, and, as opposed to rolling or floating, scrapes his body against the floor as he inches his way out of the room.</text>
						</event>
